Veg biryani recipe:
- Mix together carrot, cauliflower, beans, mushrooms, peas, potatoes, mint, coriander, fried onions, ginger garlic paste, and curd (500 gms). Add salt to taste, 1 tsp red chilli powder, and 2 tsp veg biryani masala.
- Marinate for at least an hour.
- Boil water and add 1 glass of rice, salt, 1 tsp ghee, 2 cinnamon sticks, 2-3 cardamom, 1 black cardamom, 3-4 cloves. Cook until 80% done.
- In a pan, add 2 tsp ghee, 1 tsp jeera, and fried onions (1 cup).
- Add the marinated mixture and cook it for 5 minutes, stirring continuously.
- Cover it and cook for another 15-20 minutes until veggies are done. Saute the paneer and add to the pan.
- Layer rice and garnish with fried onions, fresh mint leaves, saffron milk, and fried cashews. 
- Cover and cook for another 10-15 mins.
- Veg biryani is ready. Serve hot. Enjoy 😊
